<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1959,2019]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,283]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,310,1959,1983]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[841,950,1959,1983]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, based on seven (
<specimenCount box="[1146,1271,1959,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" type="female">six females</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1328,1428,1959,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="584" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
) individuals captured with sweep nets in sandy areas in the Natural and Historical Reserve of 
<collectingCountry box="[1146,1185,1995,2019]" name="Iceland" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Isla</collectingCountry>
Martín García (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1420,1995,2019]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1851,1875]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-18@1.[151,1436,181,1827]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Geographic distribution of Heterostylum ferrugineum (Fabricius) (circles) and H. hirsutum (Thunberg) (triangles). White symbols: new records; black symbols: previous distributions." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026866/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="584">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). This small island (168 ha) lies at the confluence of the 
<collectingCountry box="[725,818,152,176]" name="Uruguay" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and Paraná rivers and is an outcrop of the crystalline basement, with different vegetational 
<typeStatus box="[504,560,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">types</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ferretti, N. &amp; Perez-Miles, F. &amp; Gonzalez, A." box="[573,776,187,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" pagination="481 - 491" refId="ref2079" refString="Ferretti, N., Perez-Miles, F. &amp; Gonzalez, A. (2010) Mygalomorph spiders of the Natural and Historical Reserve of Martin Garcia Island, Rio de la Plata River, Argentina. Zoological Studies, 49 (4), 481 - 491." type="journal article" year="2010">
Ferretti 
<emphasis box="[660,706,187,211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="585">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens captured at this site expands the southern end of the species distribution more than 
<quantity box="[548,651,223,248]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" unit="km" value="1000.0">1,000 km</quantity>
. The females were captured hovering at 
<quantity box="[1084,1191,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="585" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 cm</quantity>
above the soil surface, possibly searching for nests of solitary bees.
</paragraph>
